A group, Coalition of Concerned Citizens of Sokoto State, has advised President Muhammadu Buhari to be cautious and extraordinarily careful in selecting his new ministers. This was just as the group urged President Buhari to appoint Sen. Aliyu Magatakarda Wamakko as a minister representing Sokoto State. The group noted this in a statement by its Coordinator, Squadron Leader Aminu Bala Sokoto (Rtd). OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE The group recalled that Wamakko’s leadership qualities earned APC resounding successes during the 2019 general elections, not in Sokoto State alone, but across Nigeria. It said, “Wamakko is always seen as a leader without borders. Therefore, being appointed a minister and as the state’s representative, he will certainly continue to uplift the party’s fortunes. “As Senator representing Sokoto North, Wamakko becomes constrained and limited to only his senatorial district.” The group also noted that the reappointment of Abba Kyari as Chief of Staff to the President and Mr. Boss Mustapha as Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF) would help in the consolidation of the laudable, meaningful programmes and policies of the Federal Government. 'Buhari’s re-appointment of Kyari, Mustapha apt' Tambuwal’s defection, political suicide, says group Buhari condoles Sokoto over Wamakko''s death Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin